ur latest,\nstate-of-the-art techniques for bulge magnitude & Sersic index computations and\nthe most recent updates of the MBH - Lsph, MBH - nsph , MBH - PA relations and\nthe FP-BH produce consistent results in the low mass regime. We establish a\nmultiple method approach for predicting BH masses in the regime where their\nspheres-of- grav. influence cannot be spatially resolved. Our approach\nmitigates against outliers from any one relation and provides a more robust\naverage prediction. We will use our new method to revisit more IMBH candidates\nin LLAGN\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Dec 2016 18:26:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Jan 2017 11:08:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-26"}
